content: Yesterday's walk to the Seine and back. Part 1 of 6 (took maybe too many photos, haha, will not post all of them today).

photos.alt: A photo of a pedestal with a vase on top, working as a fence post, located on the top of a terrace, overlooking a view. There is a big hill on the horizon, and a silhouette of an Eiffel Tower slightly visible. The weather is overcast, with grey cloud, and it is very slightly raining.

A landscape photo of a terraceâ€™s viewpoint overlooking the suburbs of Paris. A metal black fence goes around its edge, there is some grass, many small buildings beyond, and grey clouds over the hilly horizon.
A photo of the river Seine from above, its small part peeking from between tall green trees. There is some out-of-focus vegetation on the foreground. Some of the trees become to yellow.

A photo of a beginning of the descend from a large hill, with a stone bench, lamp posts and low metal chain fence. Metal railings can be seen in the middle, stone fence on the right. Far beyond, downhill, a wide road can be seen with tiny cars, and more trees going up to the horizon.
